Nollywood veteran actress, Rita Edochie has condemned the fight between Bianca Ojukwu and the outgoing First Lady of Anambra State, Ebelechi Obiano at the inauguration of Prof Charles Soludo as the next Governor of the state. DAILY POST reported that drama ensued on Thursday at the inauguration of Prof Soludo when the wife of outgoing Governor Willie Obiano, Ebelechukwu, and Mrs Bianca Ojukwu engaged in a physical fight during the event. Mrs Obiano stepped in and moved to the front row where the widow of Dim Odumegwu Ojukwu uttered some words. While talking, Bianca stood up and appeared to slap her. Immediately, aides and other personalities intervened in the matter and stopped the women from further attacks. This happened immediately Soludo took his oath of office. Reacting to the incident which has stirred reactions online, the actress described the fight as a disgrace to Anambra State. She wrote: “Tell everybody to shut down. “What a disgrace on this day in Anambra state.”